    {
      "id": "cf6a42c5c587e044e92a1f9e645e0d9dab67c07b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-19 18:46:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 9: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nThis looks usable to me.  I don't know all the details of the RPM building, but the packages built and tested correctly in autotest.\n\nBrian, Chris, can you please inspect.  I think at this stage of 2.4 development we are looking for \"workable\" rather than \"perfect\".",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "e3884fd5a0e7dee7a40d2eaedcfd4626dcf390df",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-19 19:51:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 9: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nLots of duplication in the various %post functions, which in an of itself is not a problem since it winds up being duplication across several RPMs.\n\nBut from a maintenance perspective, this is almost screaming for some kind of common function library.\n\nThat's not nearly enough to prevent landing though.  Just thought for the future.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "42ab112c12e85e592783600638730a9b0465d769",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-19 22:18:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 9:\n\nAndreas, I'll look at the patch in a moment.  First I need to mention how much I disagree with the statement that we just need something that is \"workable\" for now.\n\nThe upstream build system hasn't worked for LLNL for years, and it doesn't need to be that way.  We need to apply the same level of code review to the build system that we do for the rest of Lustre.\n\nFurther, I would _much_ rather see the LU-1199 work land for 2.4 than that this osd repackaging, or DKMS, or MIC work, etc.\n\nAll of that just makes the LU-1199 that much more difficult, and if it also done in a less-than-ideal way, that just shifts all of the burden onto LLNL to fix, and continually raises the bar on the work we need to do.\n\nSo thats a long way of saying that I think the reviews and revisions that Bruno has worked on have been essential.  And I do appreciate the work he's been doing!\n\nI have a reworked version of this patch to apply to the LU-1199 off in a branch on github:\n\n  https://github.com/chaos/lustre/commits/LU-1199-wip\n\nSo I think I'll be able to deal with this landing without too much trouble.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "8be575ea2e600430eb58f5fb9b10a2952df546bf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-19 22:34:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 9: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "d557cc0456d13fb20f185189b31c6267a7e92a06",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-19 23:47:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 9:\n\nChris, to clarify my previous comments, I totally agree with you that the code review for build changes should be as good as the review for other patches. I was commenting that _I_ cannot provide as good a review on the patch, since I don't understand the build details as well as other parts of Lustre.\n\nDefinitely I do appreciate the work you are doing to improve the Lustre build system. Since I don't understand very well what we have now, I can't necessarily contribute to the ongoing development and discussion in a meaningful way, but I'm definitely supportive of your efforts. \n\nAs for my \"good enough\" comment, that was merely a reflection that we are beyond feature freeze for 2.4 and need to start working toward a solution that can be ready in the next few weeks. We have a requirement from our legal department that we so not ship ZFS binary packages with the rest of Lustre due to license issues, and we need to work on the DKMS packaging to meet this requirement.\n\nIn summary, I'm happy that you are able to work with this patch. I agree that we will need much more work to fix the build system to your liking, but we also cannot fix it in one patch. This patch is hopefully a step in the right direction.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 9
    },
